>>>> ## What we are doing in the South East region
>>>> Diabetes UK South East is made up of a team of staff plus a wide network
>>>> There are 9 million people living across the south east of England, with
over 640,000 people living with diabetes. We work locally to support people
with diabetes and those at risk of developing diabetes to live well.
>>>> Collaborating with our Diabetes UK Local Groups, amazing volunteers and
Diabetes Voices, we have achieved many successes across campaigning,
>>>> We work closely with key decision makers to ensure that people with
>>>> ### Working with healthcare professionals and staff across the NHS
>>>> We raise awareness and knowledge of diabetes across the NHS to ensure
>>>> We work with our volunteers to raise awareness of diabetes and the work
of Diabetes UK, by providing talks to schools, businesses and community
>>>> We work with and support Diabetes UK local groups who provide local
support to people with diabetes. We put on events to give people with diabetes
the skills and knowledge to manage their diabetes.
>>>> We help people across the region to raise vital money to help improve the
lives of people with diabetes and fund important research into diabetes.
